Who We Are

Meet Jules & Riley

The human-canine dream team behind every muddy, joyful, tail-wagging adventure across South Manchester.

Every dog deserves to feel part of the squad.

Jules has been walking dogs professionally across the Chorlton area for years, building a loyal squad of four-legged regulars who know the fields, paths and puddles of South Manchester better than most humans.

With Riley leading the charge (usually towards the nearest mud), every walk is a proper adventure. Whether it's a frosty morning at Turn Moss, a sunny romp through Chorlton Ees, or a rainy plod through Longford Park, the squad gets out in all conditions — because happy dogs don't check the weather forecast.

Small group sizes mean every dog gets proper attention, socialisation with their mates, and the kind of exercise that leaves them snoozing contentedly until teatime.

What We Offer

Services

From group adventures to solo strolls, dogs and cats covered — come rain, shine, or sideways Manchester drizzle.

Group Walk

The full squad experience. Your dog joins a small group of compatible pals for a proper 60-minute adventure across our favourite green spaces. Maximum 5 dogs ensures everyone gets attention and space to explore. Every dog comes home showered and towel dried.

£15 / walk

Solo Walk

One-on-one time for dogs who prefer their own company, need extra attention, or are still building confidence. A dedicated 30-minute walk at your dog's own pace and comfort level.

£18 / walk

Pop-In / Puppy Visit

A home visit including a 15-minute walk — perfect for puppies, older dogs, or if you're stuck at work a bit longer than planned. Toilet breaks, feeding, a bit of company and some fresh air.

£18 / visit

Cat Visit

A 10–15 minute visit to feed, let out, play, and change the litter. Daily pics and updates so you know your feline friend is happy while you're away.

£10 / visit

Double Cat Visit

Two visits in the same day — morning and evening, or whatever schedule suits your cat best. Same great care, twice the cuddles.

£17 / day
Where We Walk

Our Stomping Grounds

The green spaces the squad knows inside out — every shortcut, every good sniffing spot, every puddle worth jumping in.

Turn Moss

Wide open playing fields perfect for a proper run-about. Frosty mornings here are magical — the squad loves it when the grass crunches underfoot.

Chorlton Ees

Meadows, woodland and the River Mersey. Proper countryside feel right in the city. Muddy paths guaranteed — bring your sense of adventure (and a towel).

Whalley Range & Old Trafford

Local parks and green spaces perfect for the squad. Great paths, friendly faces, and always something new to sniff. Convenient pick-up and drop-off for the neighbourhood.
